name: Strawberry Cupcakes
author: Aini
summary: Strawberry cupcakes with real fresh strawberry bits!
ingredients: ¼ cup finely chopped fresh strawberries, drained
directions: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C)
Grease 12 cupcake pan cups or line with paper liners
In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy
Beat in the eggs one at a time, then stir in the strawberry extract
Combine the self-rising flour and salt; stir into the batter just until blended
Spoon the batter into the prepared cups, dividing evenly
Bake in the preheated oven until the tops spring back when lightly pressed, 20 to 25 minutes
Cool in the pan set over a wire rack
When cool, arrange the cupcakes on a serving platter
